cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR 

This paper deals with the task of identifying and localizing abnormalities in radiology images, which is a common problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a unified approach that uses limited location annotations, which involves machine learning techniques such as deep learning and optimization. This suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with medical imaging, which is a subfield of multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
